Create 6 Measures

      


Click on this icon located on the top left side of the page to download the document containing the measures è

I have added numbers to the measure names to indicate the recommended order in which to create them.


Follow either one of the following 2 options to add all 6 measures:

Option 1: Measures can be created by typing in the DAX calculation.

1.    Click on the “New Measure” icon

2.    Delete the default (Measures =) content on the DAX formula bar

3.    Type in the calculation onto the DAX formula bar in this format àMeasure Name = DAX Formula

4.    Hit Enter


Option 2: Measures can also be pasted directly onto the DAX formula bar

1.    Click on the “New Measure” icon

2.    Delete the default (Measures =) content on the DAX formula bar

3.    Copy and Paste in the entire contents of the measure directly onto the DAX formula bar.

4.    Hit Enter


Final Touches: Configure the following Measures in the Measure tools “Formatting” field;

1.    1.AnnualCostPerPatient =  Click on $ sign, and change decimal place to 2

2.    2.YoY%CostPerPatient =  Click on % sign, and change decimal place to 2

3.    4.PatientPenetrationRate = Click on % sign, and change decimal place to 2

4.    5.YoY%PatientRetention = Click on % sign, and change decimal place to 2



Organizing measures can help eliminate stress and frustration in Power BI. It’s a good practice to either add a period (.) or number them to have them appear on top of your list of columns.
